          // IMPLEMENTED: readable note — policy binder
          "id": "policy_binder",
          "type": "notes",
          "name": "Albion Policy Binder",
          "takeable": false,
          "readable": true,
          "text": "MERIDIAN CYBER INSURANCE — Policy Ref: MC-2023-ALBE-007\n\nINSURING CLAUSE: Meridian indemnifies the Insured for losses arising from a Cyber Event, including physical loss or damage arising directly from a Cyber Event (affirmative cyber — LMA21 compliant).\n\nWARRANTY SCHEDULE (selected):\nW-03 — Patch Management: Patches applied within 90 days or deferred with compensating controls within 30 days. NOTE: IEC 61511 safety-certified systems may defer patching pending recertification, provided compensating controls are documented and implemented.\nW-07 — IT/OT Network Segmentation: Segmentation maintained to prevent direct protocol-level IT-to-OT access. Remediation deadline: 12 months post-inception [EXPIRED — 4 MONTHS BEFORE INCIDENT]. Extension request under review.\nW-09 — Access Control: User accounts deprovisioned within 5 business days of departure.\nW-12 — MSP Security: Managed service providers maintain equivalent security standards.\n\nEXCLUSIONS — Section 5.4 (Act of War): Losses caused by war or state-backed cyber operations conducted in the course of war. LMA5567A. Peacetime state-sponsored operations require 'major detrimental impact' threshold analysis.\n\nCOOPERATION CLAUSE — Section 7.1: The Insured must preserve all forensic evidence before restoring, rebuilding, or reimaging any affected system.",
