          "takeable": false,
          "readable": true,
          "text": "FORMAL INCIDENT NOTIFICATION — Meridian Claims Portal\nFiled by: James Whitworth, Facility Manager, Albion Energy Storage Ltd\nTime: T+75 minutes after emergency shutdown (within 48-hour SLA)\n\nIncident type: Confirmed cyber intrusion — SCADA/ICS systems\nSystems affected: PLC-BMS, SIS safety PLC, enterprise IT network\nPhysical damage: Battery cell thermal degradation in Racks A1-A4 (cells did not reach full thermal runaway)\nContainment: Manual ESD activated; jump server Ethernet cable removed; site network isolated\nRegulatory: NCSC verbal notification in progress; NIS written notification pending\n\nESTIMATED TOTAL LOSS: £8,200,000 (provisional)\n  Incident response costs: £1,400,000\n  Business interruption (6-week outage, Grid ESO penalties): £4,800,000\n  Physical equipment damage (battery cell replacement): £1,600,000\n  Third-party — Trent Water Services investigation: £400,000\n\nNote: Facility offline approx. 6 weeks during forensic investigation and SIS recertification.",
          "observations": "James Whitworth's formal incident notification. Filed by Albion's facility manager via Meridian Claims Portal at T+75 minutes.",
